First Department,

May, 1976

(May 4, 1976) In the Matter of Samuel L. Zeigen, Appellant, v Leonard E. Yoswein, as Commissioner of the Department of Rent and Housing Maintenance in the Housing and Development Administration of the City of New York, Respondent, and Sloan Realty Co., Intervenor-Respondent.

Judgment, Supreme Court, New York County, entered on May 20, 1975, unanimously affirmed for the reasons stated by Fine, J., at Special Term. Respondents shall recover of appellant one bill of $60 costs and disbursements of this appeal. Concur—Kupferman, J. P., Lupiano, Birns, Silverman and Nunez, JJ.
